<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-06-0761 </DOCNO><TEXT>The discovery of natural gas and coal reserves in Bangladesh has raisedhopes that that country, one of the poorest in the world, could beginto make important economic and social progress. Exploitation of theseresources requires financial assistance from the developed world, however.This paper reviews the contribution already made by foreign aid and thepotential sources for future funding for electric power generation, transmissionand distribution. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>